cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.HC 

The paper focuses on feature extraction and computer vision tasks related to facial beauty prediction. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also utilizes deep neural networks and Bayesian ridge regression, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves human-computer interaction and perception of facial beauty, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) due to the use of deep learning techniques.
